      "writtenOn": "2026-04-28T09:56:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "With `o_errCode`, callers need to:\n1. Create a error code variable\n2. Pass it by reference to this utility API\n3. Check return value of the utility API\n4. Check if any error code has been set\n\nWith `std::expected\u003cbool, errCode\u003e`:\nCallers need to check the returned value from the utility API.\n\nUsing `std::expected\u003c\u003e` is a more modern C++ approach, makes the utility API more readable and reduces burden on the caller.",
      "parentUuid": "8adeec07_649b8bee",
      "revId": "6900f9046023c8e937876f2ff43bd8da0e3f2bc0",
