      "message": "@anupama.b.r1@ibm.com Some fundamental issue. When API is setting error codes why it needs to return a boolean? Error code itself can give info that it was not found or failed.\nAlso, that is what your statements tells in the Todo \"return false and update o_errCode\".\n\n@souvikroyofficial10@gmail.com What are we benefiting from moving to std::Expected here?\n\n* We still need to create a variable to hold the value returned in std::expected?\n\nIMO std::expected is best suited when the return values are exclusive not when they mean same thing.",
      "parentUuid": "42fd19be_588fb877",
      "revId": "6900f9046023c8e937876f2ff43bd8da0e3f2bc0",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
